Las Vegas Fire and Rescue get some help from @mayoroflasvegas to show the importance of firework safety while using safe and sane fireworks.🎆 

They also blew up some watermelons to show just how dangerous illegal fireworks can be. 

You can report illegal fireworks at iSpyFireworks.com.

node.text:
It’s “day of the cowboy” and we salute Las Vegas’ favorite cowboy: Vegas Vic.  He has been watching over Fremont Street for 70 years this year. 

This week, the City Council approved a Retail Lease with Vic’s Symphony Park for the development of a full service restaurant and tavern with the iconic Vegas Vic’s brand in #DTLV. 
 
The restaurant and lounge will span 6,300 square feet and feature a replica of Vegas Vic.

Photo by City of Las Vegas on July 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'THIS WEEK, THE CITY COUNCIL APPROVED ARETAIL LEASE WITH VIC'S SYMPHONY PARK, LLC, FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF A FULL SERVICE RESTAURANT AND TAVERN WITH THE ICONIC VEGAS VIC'S BRAND IN DOWNTOWN LAS VEGAS. THE RESTAURANT AND LOUNGE WILL SPAN 6,300 SQUARE FEET AND FEATURE A REPLICA OF VEGAS VIC. @cityoflasvegas'.

Introducing The Arrow! The Arrow is a free shuttle service that will connect guests of the Courtyard Homeless Resource Center to 19 essential public & private service sites 🚐.

The service, operated by Keolis, will run seven days a week from 8:30 a.m. to 6:30 p.m. Today the ribbon cutting ceremony was held outside City Hall.

Learn more at lasvegasnevada.gov/arrow.
